                    <span>I am an MBA student and the book, Competitive Advantage, by Michael Porter is one of the best books I have read on the theory of sustaining competitive advantage. The text illustrates the five forces theory and the generic strategies which companies must use as analytical tools in designing the right strategy to maintain supremacy in their field.<P>I recommend this book to anyone interested in gaining fantastic insight into Michael Porter's theories of competition.</span>
                  
